  "conclusion": "For c5, adding per-row MoE, post-attention, O projection, KV append, input, QKV, scratch, or input+QKV on top of context-only per-row replay does not repair the tail row. Explicit native rowchunk2, however, restores generated-token equality for c5/c6/c7 with default output=batch and tail-GEMV metadata. The rows>=5 residual is therefore a full-attention row-grouping/no-rowchunk interaction that rowchunk2 avoids, not a simple single-stage suffix or pre-QKV fallback on top of per-row context. No throughput claim is made.",
  "created_at": "2026-06-03T21:17:13Z",
